title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>I am eager to see the new <fr:link
type="local"
href="tfmt-000R.xml"
addr="tfmt-000R"
title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes">forests</fr:link> <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-009H.xml"
addr="jms-009H"
title="List of forests">that people create</fr:link> using <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-005P.xml"
addr="jms-005P"
title="Forester">Forester</fr:link>. I am happy to offer personal assistance via the <fr:link
type="external"
href="https://lists.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forester-discuss">mailing list</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:p>Many aspects of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-005P.xml"
addr="jms-005P"
title="Forester">Forester</fr:link> are in flux and not fully documented; it will often be instructive to consult the source of existings <fr:link
type="local"
href="tfmt-000R.xml"
addr="tfmt-000R"
title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes">forests</fr:link>, such as <fr:link
type="external"
href="https://github.com/jonsterling/forest">my own</fr:link>. Please be aware that my own <fr:link
type="local"
href="tfmt-000R.xml"
addr="tfmt-000R"
title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes">forest</fr:link> tends to be using the latest (often unreleased) version of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-005P.xml"
addr="jms-005P"
title="Forester">Forester</fr:link>, so there may be slight incompatibilities.</fr:p><fr:p>Have fun, and be sure to send me links to your <fr:link
type="local"
href="tfmt-000R.xml"
addr="tfmt-000R"
title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes">forests</fr:link> when you have made them!</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
